defaultPlantlife support the
default UK’s position on 
defaultremoving
default the cap on the number of species to be included on the EU list,
default as Plantlife strongly believes the list should represent and address the scale of the environmental issue. Capping the list of IAS at 50 when there are at least 1200 across Europe will not make a strong enough impact on this growing problem and one that is causing significant harm to biodiversity. Plantlife 
defaultsupport the
